oralDict.contentDesc:
Sam had a cold because he swam with some friends yesterday afternoon. This morning he had a headache. After taking the temperature, his mother found that he had a serious fever. So she took him to see a doctor. The doctor advised Sam to take some medicine and stay in bed for two days. So Sam can't go to school and he's writing to ask for two days' sick leave. He'll go to school as soon as he gets well.

​

subContents.content: Sarah didn't feel well. She really wanted to be healthy, but she didn't know what to do. Mr. Green, a doctor, told her how to stay healthy. "First, you should look after yourself. For example, you should go for a walk after dinner, do more exercise and eat lots of fruit and vegetables. They are all good for your health. Don't watch TV too much, read in bed, eat too much or go to bed late." After that Sarah did as Mr. Green said. She is very healthy now.

voiceTextsNew: Sarah didn't feel well. She really wanted to be healthy, but she didn't know what to do. Mr. Green, a doctor, told her how to stay healthy.  First, you should look after yourself. For example, you should go for a walk after dinner, do more exercise and eat lots of fruit and vegetables. They are all good for your health. Don't watch TV too much, read in bed, eat too much or go to bed late.  After that Sarah did as Mr. Green said. She is very healthy now.
